excerpt: Casual stop with a nautical theme & indoor picnic tables for seafood, plate lunches & fish burgers.
detail_description: Paia Fish Market Restaurant is a popular eatery located at the corner of Hana Hwy. and Baldwin Ave. It's known for its casual nautical theme and focus on delicious seafood, plate lunches, and fish burgers. The restaurant offers about 6 fresh fish varieties daily, prepared in various ways until they run out. Some favorites include blackened Ahi sashimi and Cajun-style Opah burger with wasabi butter and cheese fries.
name: Paia Fish Market Restaurant
address: 100 Hana Hwy, Paia, HI 96779, USA

excerpt: Counter-serve cafe featuring farm-fresh American eats & handmade baked goods in a quaint setting.
detail_description: Leoda's Kitchen and Pie Shop is a charming counter-serve cafe located in Lahaina, offering farm-fresh American cuisine and delectable handmade baked goods. The restaurant boasts a cozy atmosphere inspired by Hawaiian plantations, where guests can indulge in a variety of savory and sweet dishes. From fresh tuna salad sandwiches to house-baked breads and locally sourced ingredients, the menu showcases an array of 'grandma comfort food' favorites.
name: Leoda's Kitchen and Pie Shop
address: 820 Olowalu Village Rd, Lahaina, HI 96761, USA

excerpt: Local landmark wins fans with its seafood-driven Hawaiian menu, Polynesian decor & epic ocean views.
detail_description: Mama's Fish House, located on Maui's north shore, is a renowned local landmark offering a seafood-driven Hawaiian menu and stunning ocean views. The restaurant has received accolades such as being a semi-finalist for the 2018 James Beard Foundation Awards and ranking as the second most popular restaurant in the U.S. on OpenTable. With daily farm-to-table deliveries, their menus constantly change to showcase fresh, locally caught fish as the star of the show.
name: Mama's Fish House
address: 799 Poho Pl, Paia, HI 96779, USA

excerpt: Acclaimed destination for Hawaiian regional cuisine features a pineapple plantation-styled setting.
detail_description: Nestled on the picturesque slopes of Haleakala in Maui's Upcountry region, Hali'imaile General Store is a renowned culinary destination offering a modern twist on Hawaiian regional cuisine. Originally a plantation store dating back to 1925, it was transformed into a restaurant in 1988 by Chef Bev Gannon and has since gained international acclaim. The restaurant prides itself on its farm-to-table dining experience, featuring locally sourced ingredients in an idyllic Upcountry setting.
name: Hali'imaile General Store
address: 900 Haliimaile Rd, Haliimaile, HI 96768, USA

excerpt: Renowned oceanfront restaurant features farm-to-table cuisine in an elegant setting with views.
detail_description: Merriman's Kapalua is a renowned oceanfront restaurant located at the point on Kapalua Bay in the Kapalua Resort. The restaurant features Hawaiian regional cuisine by James Beard award-winning Chef Peter Merriman, known for his farm-to-table commitment with over 90% of ingredients locally sourced. The elegant indoor dining area offers romantic ambiance with cozy, candlelit tables and vaulted ceilings. At sunset, diners can capture breathtaking views as the sun disappears over the ocean.
name: Merriman's Kapalua
address: 1 Bay Club Pl, Lahaina, HI 96761, USA

excerpt: Farm-to-table eatery & bar for Hawaiian food, beer & cocktails, served in a casual space.
detail_description: Monkeypod Kitchen by Merriman in Wailea, Maui is a farm-to-table restaurant and bar that offers Hawaiian cuisine, beer, and cocktails in a laid-back setting. It's a hit with both tourists and locals, especially the Whalers Village location which is always bustling. The signature Monkeypod Mai Tai made with two types of rum, lime, macadamia nut orgeat, orange curacao, and honey-lilikoi foam is not to be missed.
name: Monkeypod Kitchen by Merriman - Wailea, Maui
address: 10 Wailea Gateway Pl B-201, Kihei, HI 96753, USA

excerpt: Casual, modern pick for a sharable Filipino & Hawaiian family recipes plus a traveling dim-sum cart.
detail_description: Lineage is a casual and modern restaurant that offers a blend of Filipino and Hawaiian family recipes, along with a traveling dim-sum cart. Located in the upscale Shops at Wailea, Lineage stands out for its authentic food and inviting atmosphere. The menu has evolved to include Korean and Chinese flavors, featuring shareable dishes like Korean fried chicken, garlic Szechuan noodles, and wagyu kalbi short rib with roasted bone marrow.
name: Lineage
address: 3750 Wailea Alanui Dr, Wailea, HI 96753, USA

excerpt: Asian shared plates, noodle dishes & sake cocktails in an airy, light, wood-trimmed space.
detail_description: Nestled in Lahaina, Hawaii, Star Noodle is a beloved spot known for its Asian shared plates, noodle dishes, and sake cocktails. Since 2010, this hotspot has been serving up traditional Hawaiian comfort food in a cool space with an ocean view. The menu features a variety of shareable starter plates like smashed cucumber salads with miso-chili sauce, steamed clams with miso butter, and adobo ribs with black pepper vinegar.
name: Star Noodle
address: 1287 Front St, Lahaina, HI 96761, USA

excerpt: Bustling local counter turning out pork belly bowls, garlic noodles & other Hawaiian comfort fare.
detail_description: Tin Roof Maui is a bustling local counter located near Maui's main airport, offering a convenient entry point for travelers seeking Hawaiian comfort food. Run by renowned chef Sheldon Simeon and his wife Janice, the restaurant serves up soulful dishes that reflect Simeon's Hilo roots. The menu features local specialties such as mochiko chicken, garlic shrimp, macaroni salad, saimin noodles, and chow fun noodles.
name: Tin Roof Maui
address: 360 Papa Pl Ste 116, Kahului, HI 96732, USA

excerpt: Beachside eatery & sandy hub for pupu, fish tacos, tropical drinks, live music & people-watching.
detail_description: Hula Grill Kaanapali is a beachside eatery and bar that offers a relaxed atmosphere with pupu, fish tacos, tropical drinks, and live music. The restaurant features an authentic Hawaiian menu made with local ingredients and freshly caught seafood. Guests can enjoy the outdoor barefoot bar while taking in views of Molokai and Lanai beaches. The renowned Aloha Hour offers drink specials and a pupu menu with options like beef poke lettuce wraps and tandoori roasted shrimp.
name: Hula Grill Kaanapali
address: 2435 Kaanapali Pkwy, Lahaina, HI 96761, USA

detail_description: Nestled in Kula, Restaurant Marlow is a culinary treasure offering a diverse menu influenced by local ingredients and global flavors. Chef Jeff Scheer and his wife, Kaili, have crafted a dining experience that emphasizes fresh, locally grown produce to create dishes bursting with flavor. From signature pizzas to mouthwatering cioppino and vegetarian options like roasted root veg, there's something for every palate.
name: Marlow
address: 30 Kupaoa St A104, Makawao, HI 96768, USA

excerpt: Classic counter-service joint serving saimin, chow fun, dry noodles, manju & plate lunches.
detail_description: Sam Sato's Inc is a classic counter-service restaurant located in Wailuku, Maui. Since the 1930s, it has been a popular spot for locals and visitors alike. The restaurant is known for its affordable and hearty breakfast options, cheeseburgers, saimin, chow fun, loco moco, and plate lunches.
name: Sam Sato's Inc
address: 1750 Wili Pa Loop A, Wailuku, HI 96793, USA

excerpt: Beachside eatery known for its seafood-driven menu, tropical drinks & family-friendly vibe.
detail_description: Leilani's on the Beach is a beachside restaurant with a focus on seafood and tropical drinks, offering a family-friendly atmosphere. Situated in the heart of Kaanapali's south beach, also known as Dig-Beach, it provides an elevated ocean view along the three-mile stretch of white sand where Hawaiian royalty used to surf and play traditional games.
name: Leilani's on the Beach
address: 2435 Kaanapali Pkwy, Lahaina, HI 96761, USA

excerpt: Intimate locale on the beach features Pacific Rim & Mediterranean dishes, plus a variety of wines.
detail_description: Mala Ocean Tavern is a charming beachfront restaurant that offers a blend of Pacific Rim and Mediterranean cuisine along with an extensive selection of wines. Chef Mark Ellman, a pioneer of the Hawaii Regional Cuisine movement, presents a menu featuring dishes such as ahi bruschetta, wok-fried Hawaiian fish, and vegan mushroom Bolognese pasta made with local shiitakes. The restaurant also serves signature cocktails like the Spa Day and the LBC.
name: Mala Ocean Tavern
address: 1307 Front St, Lahaina, HI 96761, USA

excerpt: Wood-fired pizzas with organic ingredients & free-range meats, made in traditional clay ovens.
detail_description: Flatbread Company is a popular pizza joint in Paia, Vermont, known for its wood-fired pizzas made with organic ingredients and free-range meats. The restaurant has a no-reservations policy but offers 'call-ahead seating' for the waitlist. It's a family-friendly spot with a laid-back vibe and spacious outdoor patio. The menu features delicious flatbread pizzas and salads, including the Daily Specials like carne and veggie options.
name: Flatbread Company
address: 89 Hana Hwy, Paia, HI 96779, USA

excerpt: Beachfront dining with sushi & other stylish Japanese creations from Iron Chef Masaharu Morimoto.
detail_description: Morimoto Maui offers beachfront dining featuring a variety of stylish Japanese creations by Iron Chef Masaharu Morimoto. The restaurant showcases a blend of Japanese and Western-inspired cuisine, highlighting the bountiful produce of Hawaii. Situated at the Andaz Maui resort, the modern architecture takes inspiration from traditional Japanese beach houses, providing an open and airy ambiance with stunning views of the beach and ocean. In addition to sushi, the menu also features dishes prepared with fresh local ingredients.
name: Morimoto Maui
address: 3550 Wailea Alanui Dr, Wailea-Makena, HI 96753, USA

excerpt: The Fairmont Kea Lani's swanky eatery has a sugarcane-plantation-era menu in a sconce-lit space.
detail_description: K Restaurant, located in the Fairmont Kea Lani, offers a unique dining experience with its sugarcane-plantation-era menu that reflects the diverse ethnic cuisine from Maui's old plantation days. The restaurant's concept is to cook up Hawaiian, Filipino, Portuguese, Korean, Puerto Rican, and European dishes in a gourmet fashion. Executive chef Jonathan Pasion has curated a menu that showcases the culinary influences of various immigrant cultures in Hawaii.
name: K Restaurant
address: 4100 Wailea Alanui Dr, Kihei, HI 96753, USA

excerpt: Breakfasts, fish tempura, teriyaki beef & a signature chicken katsu in a simple, casual space.
detail_description: Da Kitchen, located in Kihei and Kahului, is a popular restaurant on Maui known for its generous portions of classic Hawaiian food. Despite its suburban strip-mall location, it attracts both locals and tourists with its island soul food, including signature dishes like chicken katsu and teriyaki beef. The airport location offers a wider selection, featuring traditional plate-lunch-style fare as well as burgers and sandwiches.
name: Da Kitchen
address: 1215 S Kihei Rd suite e, Kihei, HI 96753, USA

excerpt: Historic, art-filled space for elegantly plated seafood, steak & Hawaiian specialties with wine.
detail_description: Nestled in the historic town of Lahaina, Lahaina Grill has been a top dining destination for over two decades. This elegant restaurant offers a blend of locally sourced ingredients and international cooking methods to craft innovative New American cuisine. The ambiance is equally impressive, with fine china and crystal adorning the tables, vibrant paintings by renowned artist Jan Kasprzycki gracing the walls, and charming pressed tin ceilings adding to the overall inviting atmosphere.
name: Lahaina Grill
address: 127 Lahainaluna Rd, Lahaina, HI 96761, USA

excerpt: Counter-serve cafe & patio is a local go-to for breakfast deals including omelets & cinnamon rolls.
detail_description: Kihei Caffe is a popular breakfast spot located in the Kihei Kalama Village, offering a variety of delicious and filling breakfast options at reasonable prices. The menu features Hawaiian favorites like Loco Moco and Crab Cake Eggs Benedict, as well as classic dishes such as omelets and cinnamon rolls. The cafe has a cozy interior with a spacious patio for outdoor dining, making it an ideal place to enjoy freshly roasted Hawaiian coffee and hearty breakfast plates.
name: Kihei Caffe
address: 1945 S Kihei Rd, Kihei, HI 96753, USA
